OL,6,FPlaid Cymru's Mabon ap Gwynfor agreed
OL,7,Fwith his Tory counterpart about
OL,8,F"deeper and more systemic" failures
OL,9,Fbecoming a "constant feature" of the
OL,10,Fgovernment's record.
OL,12,F"Measures that should be exceptional,
OL,13,Ftemporary and used only as a last
OL,14,Fresort have instead become routine,"
OL,15,Fhe said. "It is the people of Wales
OL,16,Fwho are paying the price for that
OL,17,Ffailure."
